hopobject.body: Not in at the moment androstenedione side effects Sixteen summers ago there was a mega-budget film about to be released, but advance word was disastrous: the director had been overbearing, costs had spiralled, and it looked like a project out of control. That summer, on the eve of its projected release, I interviewed its lead actress in London for the Los Angeles Times; without any encouragement on my part, she told me what a wretched ordeal she had endured in its making, and of the callous treatment she had suffered from the director.
